+# Amazon Product Monitor
+
+A command-line tool to discover trending products on Amazon marketplace by monitoring seller pages and analyzing sales signals.
+
+## Features
+
+- **Web Scraping**: Extract product data from Amazon seller pages
+- **Trending Detection**: Identify products with high review velocity and momentum
+- **Data Storage**: SQLite database to track product history
+- **CLI Interface**: Easy-to-use command-line tool
+- **Scheduled Monitoring**: Automatic periodic monitoring with APScheduler
+- **Multiple Output Formats**: JSON and CSV export
+
+## Installation
+
+```bash
+git clone <repo-url>
+cd amazon-product-monitor
+pip install -r requirements.txt
+```
+
+## Usage
+
+### Monitor Amazon Seller Page
+```bash
+python3 -m app.cli --seller-url "https://amazon.com/s?i=merchant-xxx" --output json
+```
+
+### Export Trending Products
+```bash
+python3 -m app.cli --trending --since "2 days" --output csv
+```
+
+### Product History
+```bash
+python3 -m app.cli --export --product-id "B0XXXXXX" --output csv
+```
+
+## Project Structure
+
+```
+app/
+├── __init__.py        # Package initialization
+├── config.py          # Configuration settings
+├── scraper.py         # Web scraping module
+├── product_analyzer.py # Product analysis & trending detection
+├── database.py        # SQLite database operations
+├── cli.py             # Command-line interface
+└── scheduler.py       # Task scheduling
+```
+
+## Requirements
+
+- Python 3.10+
+- requests >= 2.31.0
+- beautifulsoup4 >= 4.12.0
+- click >= 8.1.0
+- APScheduler >= 3.10.0
